  m_Name: Cleidobrachial_muscle_Clavicular_part_of_deltoid.L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Cleidobrachial_muscle_Clavicular_part_of_deltoid.L
  partName: Cleidobrachial muscle Clavicular part of deltoid Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left cleidobrachial muscle, representing the clavicular part of the deltoid
    group, extends between the clavicular region and the brachium of the canine forelimb.
    This muscle assists primarily in advancing the limb forward and flexing the shoulder
    joint during locomotion.
  - It plays an important role in coordinated forelimb movement, especially during
    walking, running, and climbing activities requiring controlled shoulder action.
    The muscle also contributes to shoulder stabilization and helps maintain smooth
    transitions between limb positions. Working with neighboring muscles, it improves
    overall forelimb precision and mobility.
